title: Howard Stern Sternthology (Declassified Week Vol.2) Part 1
description:
Howard Stern Sternthology (Declassified Week Vol.2) Part 1  (02:42:36)


* This Is Beetle – Richard Christy tells how he recorded Beet's legendary theme song "This Is Beetle" (6/17/2005). Followed by a "Declassified" about Jon Hein's moaning sound.
 
* Don't Forget The Stern Show Bits & Scott Party DJ - A fill in the blank Stern Show trivia game & Goofing On Scott The Engineer (11/20/2013). Followed by a "Declassified" about the origin of "Hey Now!"
 
* Eric The TNA Fan – A fan favorite request from Steve in Oregon, Where Eric The Actor Calls In & they play clips of him on a TNA show (11/7/2012). Followed by a "Declassified" uncovering some famous drops from movies.
 
* Video Game Winner – Howard meets the man who won $1M for pitching a perfect game (5/6/2010). Followed by a "Declassified" about the very first "Booey" song parody. 
 
* Benjy Fingering Recap - Howard reviews the wild day when Perez Hilton fingered Benjy's asshole (6/24/2014). Followed by a "Declassified" on a sound drop that's 86 years old!

* Pope Visits NYC – Howard is fascinated by the TV coverage of the Pope's visit (9/23/2015)
